features: 256GB 4 IN 1 PHOTO STICK - High quality aluminum frosted ZARMST usb c flash drive comes in a true 4 IN 1 Design, it has 4 built-in ports (USB-C, iPhone Port, Micro USB and Standard USB A Connector) with no additional adapters to make it more stable.

HIGH SPEED TRANSMISSION CHIP - ZARMST Memory Stick provides an easy and fast way to transfer all kinds of files. Up to 80M/S Read and 30M/S Write Speeds. ZARMST allows you to release the memory on your storage device offline without a data cable or cloud.(Performance may vary based on host device, interface, usage conditions, and other factors).

ULTIMATE COMPATIBILITY - One end is USB Type C interface and a 3 in 1 interface on the other, which is not only for most IOS devices (such as iPhone, iPad, Macbook) Android devices (Type C or Old Style Micro USB models), but also all kinds of traditional USB interface devices (laptops, tablets, TV’s, car audio systems, and more), lets you easily transfer files back and forth between different devices.

APP FOR EASY FILE MANAGEMENT - Easily manage files on your IOS device with the LUV-Share app, it allows you view, access and back up all the files in your phone's memory in one place, available in the App Store. One-click back-up albums and address book, and encrypted files function are all included.

ZARMST 5 YEAR WARRANTY - All of 256 gb ZARMST Pen Drives have been rigorously tested and formatted before leaving the factory. And we provide 5 Years warranty service. Questions will be responded to within 24 hours.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: What devices does the ZARMST work with? It will work with iPhone (iOS 9.0 or later), for Samsung Galaxy Series & Note Devices 6 Series and ABOVE, Windows and Macbook, Google Pixel and more. In short, ZARMST photo stick is a portable universal storage drive. Where is the iPhone connector? The connector for iPhone and the micro connector are hidden in the standard Type-A USB (2 in 1). With the logo side up, plug the connector into your device when you use the iPhone connector. Does ZARMST work with phone cases? For a better experience, please remove your phone protective cases if necessary before using ZARMST photo stick. Do I need to install an application to use ZARMST ? For iPhone, you NEED TO INSTALL THE "LUV-SHARE" APP in the App Store before inserting ZARMST. For Android and other devices,plug and play, find the file manager of the corresponding device to manage the files.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Versatile and Reliable: A Must-Have OTG USB Drive!
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the 256GB OTG USB, and it has proven to be an absolute game-changer. Its seamless compatibility with both phones and computers makes it a versatile solution for my data storage needs.The plug-and-play functionality is a standout feature, allowing me to effortlessly transfer files between my smartphone and laptop without any hassle. The generous 256GB storage capacity ensures that I have ample space for all my documents, photos, and videos.The build quality is commendable; this usb drive feels sturdy and durable. The compact design is perfect for on-the-go use, fitting easily into my pocket or bag. The transfer speeds are impressive, saving me valuable time when moving large files.Whether you're a professional needing to share work files between devices or a casual user looking for a reliable storage solution, this usb drive is a fantastic choice. I highly recommend it for its convenience, speed, and ample storage capacity. It has truly simplified my digital life!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely a Life Saver!!!!
reviews.reviewText: I was A bit hesitant to purchase something so compact for my devices, but I wanted to take the risk. This flashdrive is the most neatest thing I’ve purchased thus far and I don’t regret it. It holds up to 256gb of storage, the overview does mention that it’s a 4-in-1 drive and couldn’t determine if it will fit for my iPhone (13 pro). I’m so happy that it does!! On the end for the computer slot of the drive, you have to carefully pull back a little piece of it for the tiny slot that works for newer model iPhones. Be careful when pulling it back. Installation was easy, color options are decent, and fast shipping. There’s a free app you have to download in your Apple/Google Play Store for it to work correctly but other than that 10/10!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Regret Giving it a Second Shot
reviews.reviewText: ** Updated Review **I decided to give this product another shot and buy another flash drive because there was a coupon and so many reviews were raving that I thought it might have just been the flash drive I received that was faulty. I received a new one and it worked very well at first (better than the first one) Now I go to use it a few weeks after and instantly had issues with my iPhone not recognizing the device anymore but I got my computer to access it so it was fine. I try again on different mobile devices and eventually, it starts working again only for my files to glitch and completely disappear .... now after going back in, thankfully a lot of the files are still there but there are countless files that now appear to be in the drive but I am unable to access them and they will not open. I am absolutely heartbroken to lose these files and regret trusting in the second device and that is my mistake. I would absolutely not recommend buying this product as it has now failed me twice and I have lost access to my important videos that I do not think I will be able to get back.Old Review:This product works pretty great at first but within my first night of installing stuff I already started to receive an “error” message when trying to access items directly after putting them on the device. I am unable to access these items and they are still taking up storage on the device despite not being able to access them. When I attempted to delete the items it won’t allow me and therefore is still taking up storage. I have been able to upload a few other items without this issue but now every time I try to upload something it does not work and I get the error message. Now I am worried it will get to the point where I am unable to access the other items as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works once you figure it out
reviews.reviewText: The instructions were truly unhelpful. I finally figured, what the heck, if I break it, I break it - and snapped the sides of the USB port backward. Lo and behold, the iPhone port was revealed. Once inserted correctly, it was easy enough to select and copy the pictures onto the drive using the Easy Flash Pro App - freeing up space on my phone. Picture attached so others can see how it is supposed to work.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars worked well and sufficiently
reviews.reviewText: i have an iphone 12 pro max, i had about 13,000 videos and photos and i couldn’t open my internal storage without it loading for a very long time within the app so instead i copied over my photos to the flash drive. it took me personally about 3 hours to move all of the photos. which i’m not mad about since it was 90 gbs worth of media. it seemed to have worked very well and i plan to do it again once my storage is too much. gave me about 60+ extra gbs of free storage.
